narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was alright. The texts and films are pretty good, but it is also a lot of grammar which gets tiresome.

I mean, it's pretty likely that if you're considering taking this course you have to either way, either to get the language requirement to graduate without starting a new language or just to be allowed to start the French major. So, you should take it. It's not super awesome in content but is a magnificent course in order to review French grammar/brush up on your reading/writing skills before doing something more intense.Go for it. You'll be fine, and if you actually pay attention/show up/do you're work it's hard to do poorly in this class.

A good solid way to consolidate skills in French. It was very writing intensive, we wrote 5 redactions and both my grammar and writing have improved a lot. You also walk out of the class with a repertoire of french short stories, films and plays under your belt. My oral, although it did improve, did not improve as much as my writing.
A run of the mill language course that truly challenged my writing ability, though I still wish we had done more work on conversational skills.
If you don't keep taking a language class, at one point you're going to completely forget that language so yes
